# Trivy ignore file — HIGH/CRITICAL findings on Cargo.lock that cannot
# currently be remediated by a dependency bump. Each entry records the
# dependency path, why no fix is reachable, and what an upstream fix needs.
#
# Keep this in sync with .cargo/audit.toml (cargo-audit uses RUSTSEC IDs;
# Trivy uses the GHSA/CVE aliases below).

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# hickory-proto 0.25.2 — NSEC3 closest-encloser proof validation enters an
# unbounded loop on cross-zone responses. (RUSTSEC-2026-0118)
#
# Dependency path:
#   hickory-proto 0.25.2
#     -> hickory-resolver 0.25.2
#       -> libp2p-dns 0.44.0 / libp2p-mdns 0.48.0
#         -> libp2p 0.56.0 -> strata-p2p
#
# Why unfixable: no patched 0.25.x release exists. The fix landed only
# after the code moved to the hickory-net crate (>= 0.26.1). The latest
# published libp2p-dns 0.44.0 / libp2p-mdns 0.48.0 still pin
# hickory-proto ^0.25.2, so the 0.26 line is unreachable via semver.
#
# Required fix: libp2p must release a version that bumps hickory to 0.26,
# then this workspace bumps libp2p. Upstream bump in flight:
#   https://github.com/libp2p/rust-libp2p/pull/6395
#   https://github.com/libp2p/rust-libp2p/issues/6412
#
# Risk: low. hickory is reached only via libp2p peer-discovery / DNS
# paths; this codebase does not perform DNSSEC validation on untrusted
# records.
GHSA-3v94-mw7p-v465

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# yamux 0.12.1 — remote panic via malformed Data frame with SYN set and an
# oversized body length (> DEFAULT_CREDIT). (CVE-2026-32314)
#
# Dependency path:
#   yamux 0.12.1
#     -> libp2p-yamux 0.47.0 (renamed dep `yamux012`, package = "yamux",
#        req "^0.12.1" — kept for the legacy WindowUpdateMode API)
#       -> libp2p 0.56.0 -> strata-p2p
#
# Note: the same CVE also affected the yamux 0.13.x instance pulled by
# libp2p-yamux; that one has been bumped to 0.13.10 and is now fixed. Only
# the 0.12.x compat dependency remains.
#
# Why unfixable: the fix exists only in yamux 0.13.10; there is no patched
# 0.12.x release. libp2p-yamux 0.47.0 (latest published) still declares a
# second, renamed `yamux012` dependency on yamux ^0.12.1, so the 0.13 line
# cannot satisfy it.
#
# Required fix: libp2p-yamux must release a version that drops the
# yamux 0.12 compatibility shim, then this workspace bumps libp2p.
#
# Risk: low for this codebase, despite the CVE being a remotely
# reachable, unauthenticated panic (CVSS 8.7). libp2p-yamux 0.47.0
# dispatches between two Yamux backends: an unmodified
# `yamux::Config::default()` resolves to yamux 0.13, and the yamux 0.12
# (`Config012`) branch is selected only when the application mutates the
# muxer config via a `set_*` call. strata-p2p builds its transport with
# bare `yamux::Config::default()` (crates/p2p/src/swarm/mod.rs) and never
# configures it, so the live path is yamux 0.13 — already bumped to the
# patched 0.13.10. The vulnerable yamux 0.12 code path is linked but not
# reachable at runtime.
CVE-2026-32314
